  "text": "To determine the localization of molecules in specific organelles, it is important to choose an appropriate cell system that has high spatial resolution of organelles in perinuclear regions [early endosome (EE), RE and Golgi] . To determine the localization of b 1 -AR in dormant and activated states, we used COS-1 cells. Because of the unique spatial organization of organelles in COS-1 cells, RE is exclusively confined within the ring-shaped structure of the Golgi (Golgi ring) and the organelles associated with degradation [EE, late endosome (LE) and lysosome] are excluded from inside the Golgi ring [CITATION_1] .",
